1
00:00:07,549 --> 00:00:08,800
[lighter flicks]

2
00:00:18,936 --> 00:00:20,562
[exhales]

3
00:00:33,325 --> 00:00:35,369
[exhales]

4
00:00:37,538 --> 00:00:40,457
Ah, shit. I really thought
you'd do better than this.

5
00:00:42,125 --> 00:00:43,126
[clicks tongue]

6
00:00:48,173 --> 00:00:49,967
Why are you giving me this?

7
00:00:50,050 --> 00:00:53,011
Sunok, I think I really like you.

8
00:00:53,095 --> 00:00:54,221
You like me?

9
00:00:54,304 --> 00:00:55,305
Yeah.

10
00:00:59,309 --> 00:01:01,770
[Sunok giggles]
Hold on.

11
00:01:01,853 --> 00:01:03,605
[Male News Reporter] <i>Up next...</i>

12
00:01:03,689 --> 00:01:05,649
[Friend A] Pretty sure it's my turn.

13
00:01:05,732 --> 00:01:07,359
And here's the ribbon!

14
00:01:07,442 --> 00:01:08,527
[Friend B] Whoa!

15
00:01:08,610 --> 00:01:10,821
[Male News Reporter] <i>In an effort</i>
<i>to boost areas hit hard by the decline</i>

16
00:01:10,904 --> 00:01:12,114
<i>of the coal industry...</i>

17
00:01:12,197 --> 00:01:13,532
Hey, where's Sunok?

18
00:01:13,615 --> 00:01:14,950
- Mm, not sure.
- [Friend B] I don't know where she is.

19
00:01:15,033 --> 00:01:16,159
GOLD LAND HOTEL & RESORT CONSTRUCTION SITE

20
00:01:16,243 --> 00:01:17,744
- [Friend A] Sunok needs to see this.
- [Friend B] She must be somewhere.

21
00:01:19,413 --> 00:01:20,664
[drum clangs]

22
00:01:21,832 --> 00:01:24,585
[gagging and struggling]

23
00:01:29,464 --> 00:01:32,009
[short gasps]

24
00:01:32,092 --> 00:01:33,093
[Henchman A] What the...

25
00:01:33,176 --> 00:01:34,386
Shit!

26
00:01:34,469 --> 00:01:35,470
[Henchman B] This crazy bastard!

27
00:01:35,554 --> 00:01:36,722
[Henchman A] Hold him, hold him!

28
00:01:36,805 --> 00:01:38,390
- [Henchman B] Fuck me.
- [Henchman A] That way.

29
00:01:39,516 --> 00:01:41,018
[Chairman Ahn] Come on.

30
00:01:41,101 --> 00:01:43,437
Don't be so rash.
You're still young.

31
00:01:44,604 --> 00:01:47,065
What you should be doing is working
to pay off your debts.

32
00:01:48,275 --> 00:01:50,736
How could I ever pay it all back?

33
00:01:50,819 --> 00:01:52,696
[Chairman Ahn laughing]
I know, right?

34
00:01:52,779 --> 00:01:54,573
On your police salary?

35
00:01:55,407 --> 00:01:58,118
Well, you should've known your place
before pushing it so far.

36
00:01:58,201 --> 00:01:59,453
[Young Jinman] I know, I know.

37
00:02:00,037 --> 00:02:03,040
Just kill me,
and only me, okay?

38
00:02:03,123 --> 00:02:05,667
But please leave
that innocent woman alone.

39
00:02:05,751 --> 00:02:07,002
I'm begging you.

40
00:02:07,627 --> 00:02:09,338
You don't need to pay us back.

41
00:02:10,172 --> 00:02:11,465
At least not entirely with money.

42
00:02:13,175 --> 00:02:14,635
[Chairman Ahn] Constable Kim Jinman.

43
00:02:16,470 --> 00:02:17,471
What if...

44
00:02:20,182 --> 00:02:22,309
You became my man instead, yeah?

45
00:02:25,896 --> 00:02:28,899
[♪ dramatic music]

46
00:03:01,640 --> 00:03:04,935
[♪ music continues]

47
00:03:13,402 --> 00:03:15,237
[inhales deeply]

48
00:03:15,320 --> 00:03:16,697
[exhales]

49
00:03:20,659 --> 00:03:23,662
[♪ sad piano music]

50
00:03:45,767 --> 00:03:48,770
[♪ music continues]

51
00:04:04,077 --> 00:04:05,745
EPISODE 7
VILLAINS

52
00:04:05,829 --> 00:04:08,832
[metal detector beeping]

53
00:04:17,007 --> 00:04:18,008
[light clicks]

54
00:04:18,091 --> 00:04:19,092
[items dropping]

55
00:04:19,968 --> 00:04:21,720
Why are you here?

56
00:04:23,513 --> 00:04:24,848
H-Heeju.

57
00:04:25,307 --> 00:04:26,516
[Heeju exhales]

58
00:04:27,476 --> 00:04:29,436
I told you not to come here, didn't I?

59
00:04:30,145 --> 00:04:32,230
- The gold bars aren't here.
- [Dokyung] Let's not do this.

60
00:04:32,814 --> 00:04:35,859
Let's just take the gold
and leave together.

61
00:04:35,942 --> 00:04:37,694
[Dokyung] I already made
the deal with the buyers.

62
00:04:37,778 --> 00:04:40,447
All we need to do is go to Cambodia
and show them the gold bars.

63
00:04:40,530 --> 00:04:42,532
We'll have 100 billion won in our account!

64
00:04:43,450 --> 00:04:44,951
I'm already giving you half.

65
00:04:45,744 --> 00:04:47,162
Isn't that enough?

66
00:04:47,245 --> 00:04:49,581
- Do you really have to take it all?
- Heeju.

67
00:04:57,297 --> 00:04:58,757
Heeju, what happened to you?

68
00:05:00,175 --> 00:05:01,802
Why are you doing this?

69
00:05:06,807 --> 00:05:07,808
[exhales sharply]

70
00:05:14,523 --> 00:05:16,024
So this is what it was like.

71
00:05:17,484 --> 00:05:18,860
The place you grew up in.

72
00:05:21,112 --> 00:05:22,697
[Dokyung] You said it was hell.

73
00:05:22,781 --> 00:05:24,282
So why are you here again?

74
00:05:25,575 --> 00:05:26,701
What happened to you?

75
00:05:28,829 --> 00:05:29,830
[inhales sharply]

76
00:05:30,580 --> 00:05:32,457
Look, if this is because
of something I've done...

77
00:05:34,167 --> 00:05:36,086
...at least give me a chance
to explain myself.

78
00:05:37,170 --> 00:05:39,548
You can do that, can't you?
After all we've been through?

79
00:05:41,341 --> 00:05:42,342
Dokyung.

80
00:05:44,427 --> 00:05:45,637
Look at us right now.

81
00:05:48,223 --> 00:05:49,391
This is the reason.

82
00:05:49,975 --> 00:05:52,435
This is why we shouldn't
be together any longer.

83
00:05:54,187 --> 00:05:55,605
Nothing happened.

84
00:05:55,689 --> 00:05:57,148
And we're not bad people.

85
00:05:58,275 --> 00:05:59,901
This is just how life is.

86
00:06:01,361 --> 00:06:03,154
When you win something really big.

87
00:06:05,156 --> 00:06:06,908
You have to lose something else.

88
00:06:07,868 --> 00:06:09,369
A thing that's less precious.

89
00:06:10,328 --> 00:06:11,496
[Heeju] And quite frankly...

90
00:06:12,664 --> 00:06:15,208
...I'm the one who has the gold now.
It's mine.

91
00:06:15,292 --> 00:06:17,711
It's up to me whether I share
it with you or not.

92
00:06:19,212 --> 00:06:20,213
Heeju.

93
00:06:22,173 --> 00:06:23,216
Get out.

94
00:06:24,718 --> 00:06:26,303
And don't ever look for me again.

95
00:06:28,346 --> 00:06:29,973
[Heeju] It's true that because of you...

96
00:06:31,057 --> 00:06:33,560
...I finally got out of the hell hole
I'd been living in.

97
00:06:35,228 --> 00:06:36,980
And being with you made me happy.

98
00:06:38,315 --> 00:06:41,526
But we can't be happy together anymore.
That's why it needs to end.

99
00:07:03,256 --> 00:07:07,886
[door creaks open and closed]

100
00:07:07,969 --> 00:07:09,304
[sniffles]

101
00:07:12,849 --> 00:07:15,852
[breathing shakily]

102
00:07:18,897 --> 00:07:20,440
[camera shutter clicking]

103
00:07:20,523 --> 00:07:23,526
[indistinct quiet chattering]

104
00:07:25,236 --> 00:07:28,239
[camera shutters clicking]

105
00:07:31,076 --> 00:07:32,160
- Thank you.
- Oh.

106
00:07:32,243 --> 00:07:33,370
Thank you very much.

107
00:07:33,453 --> 00:07:34,913
[both chuckling]

108
00:07:34,996 --> 00:07:37,999
[applause]

109
00:07:39,125 --> 00:07:40,126
That's great to hear.

110
00:07:40,210 --> 00:07:42,170
[all laughing]

111
00:07:42,253 --> 00:07:44,005
- And so it begins.
- Ah, look who it is!

112
00:07:44,089 --> 00:07:45,840
Sir, you're here.

113
00:07:45,924 --> 00:07:48,343
- [Governor] Mr. Ahn.
- Thank you for coming. I know you're busy.

114
00:07:48,426 --> 00:07:49,678
Well, how could I miss it?

115
00:07:49,761 --> 00:07:51,388
It's your business, Mr. Ahn.

116
00:07:51,471 --> 00:07:52,597
[all laughing]

117
00:07:52,681 --> 00:07:54,683
Oh, right.
This is our partner from Cambodia.

118
00:07:54,766 --> 00:07:55,767
- Ah.
- Our governor.

119
00:07:55,850 --> 00:07:56,935
- How do you do?
- Nice to meet you.

120
00:07:57,018 --> 00:07:58,019
- [Governor] Congratulations.
- [Socom] Thank you.

121
00:07:58,103 --> 00:07:59,688
- [Governor] Of course.
- [Socom] Yes.

122
00:07:59,771 --> 00:08:00,939
- Thank you.
- Thank you very much.

123
00:08:01,022 --> 00:08:01,981
- [Socom] Thank you.
- [Governor] It's been a pleasure.

124
00:08:02,065 --> 00:08:03,024
[Socom] Absolutely.

125
00:08:03,108 --> 00:08:04,067
[Chairman Ahn] And this
is the congressman.

126
00:08:04,150 --> 00:08:05,777
[Politician] I've been looking forward
to meeting you.

127
00:08:05,860 --> 00:08:08,863
[Chairman Ahn chewing and slurping]

128
00:08:11,908 --> 00:08:13,868
The actors played their parts well.

129
00:08:15,161 --> 00:08:16,913
Make sure everyone keeps their mouth shut.

130
00:08:16,996 --> 00:08:18,248
No loose lips.

131
00:08:19,833 --> 00:08:21,835
And I want this deal on
the front page tomorrow.

132
00:08:21,918 --> 00:08:23,128
Understood, sir.

133
00:08:24,462 --> 00:08:25,880
Those Cambodians.

134
00:08:25,964 --> 00:08:28,049
Stick 'em in a room and keep 'em happy.

135
00:08:28,508 --> 00:08:30,552
Drugs, drinks, women, whatever it takes.

136
00:08:30,635 --> 00:08:31,970
Don't want 'em getting ideas.

137
00:08:32,053 --> 00:08:33,680
- Yes, sir.
- [Chairman Ahn slurping]

138
00:08:33,763 --> 00:08:36,307
Ah, all this bullshit
for one single casket!

139
00:08:37,183 --> 00:08:38,184
[Jinman] Hello, sir.

140
00:08:38,268 --> 00:08:39,269
It's been a while.

141
00:08:51,197 --> 00:08:52,949
Where's the casket?

142
00:08:53,033 --> 00:08:54,034
[Chairman Ahn] Who took it?

143
00:08:55,285 --> 00:08:57,829
Yeah, well, it's, uh...

144
00:08:59,456 --> 00:09:00,457
It was this woman, right?

145
00:09:02,333 --> 00:09:03,585
- Yeah.
- [Jinman] It was?

146
00:09:03,668 --> 00:09:05,962
- [Donggu] Yeah.
- Look, different name.

147
00:09:06,588 --> 00:09:08,965
[Jinman] So it wasn't Cha Yujin.
It was Kim Heeju.

148
00:09:11,634 --> 00:09:13,511
The thing is, sir,
it's just...

149
00:09:14,262 --> 00:09:16,639
...we're talkin' about one ton
of gold bars, here.

150
00:09:16,723 --> 00:09:18,475
And having to smuggle and sell it?

151
00:09:19,309 --> 00:09:21,394
I don't think anyone could do
that by themselves.

152
00:09:22,353 --> 00:09:23,438
They must have had help.

153
00:09:23,521 --> 00:09:25,190
Someone else is pulling the strings?

154
00:09:26,816 --> 00:09:27,942
Suspect anyone?

155
00:09:28,026 --> 00:09:29,277
[Jinman] We'll find out
once we investigate.

156
00:09:30,653 --> 00:09:35,533
Although, with the police being involved,
it can get pretty risky.

157
00:09:35,617 --> 00:09:36,701
Do you want cash?

158
00:09:36,785 --> 00:09:37,786
[Jinman] Well, I...

159
00:09:39,037 --> 00:09:41,831
...I do always need more money, sir.

160
00:09:42,457 --> 00:09:43,875
How much you want?

161
00:09:44,793 --> 00:09:46,711
One gold bar.
That's it.

162
00:09:46,795 --> 00:09:47,796
That's all I want.

163
00:09:49,047 --> 00:09:50,423
[Jinman] Give me a week to work on this.

164
00:09:51,674 --> 00:09:53,510
I'll find all 100 gold bars.

165
00:09:54,803 --> 00:09:56,304
Keep one for myself.

166
00:09:56,387 --> 00:10:00,517
And then I'll return
the other 99 back to you, sir.

167
00:10:01,017 --> 00:10:02,894
What do you plan to do with one gold bar?

168
00:10:02,977 --> 00:10:06,481
Well, uh, you know,
I'm getting old now.

169
00:10:07,774 --> 00:10:09,692
I'm thinking of quitting the force.

170
00:10:09,776 --> 00:10:11,611
[Jinman] I wanna buy a pawnshop.

171
00:10:11,694 --> 00:10:14,155
Sit back and take it easy.
Play loan shark.

172
00:10:14,656 --> 00:10:16,282
[Jinman] Just live like that.

173
00:10:16,366 --> 00:10:19,911
I think I've done more than enough, sir.
That's a good end for me.

174
00:10:22,455 --> 00:10:25,125
[Chairman Ahn scoffs]
Sure.

175
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:28,086
Bring the casket back,
and I'll give you one.

176
00:10:30,630 --> 00:10:31,881
[Jinman] Thank you, sir.

177
00:10:34,050 --> 00:10:35,635
If you need to get in touch,

178
00:10:35,718 --> 00:10:37,303
- go through Chief Cheon.
- Yes.

179
00:10:39,264 --> 00:10:41,975
Well, then, we have an agreement.
Excuse me.

180
00:10:44,352 --> 00:10:45,687
- [Chairman Ahn] Hey, Kim Jinman.
- Yes, sir.

181
00:10:47,230 --> 00:10:50,567
You knew about the gold all along
and you didn't lose your cool.

182
00:10:51,651 --> 00:10:52,902
[Chairman Ahn] You were first, right?

183
00:10:53,194 --> 00:10:54,279
To find out about it?

184
00:10:54,821 --> 00:10:56,739
You're the one who told Hocheol.

185
00:10:57,615 --> 00:10:58,658
But you never thought...

186
00:10:59,993 --> 00:11:02,453
"Should I just keep all the gold
and run away?"

187
00:11:02,537 --> 00:11:04,289
You never felt the urge
to do anything like that?

188
00:11:04,372 --> 00:11:05,582
[chewing]

189
00:11:06,708 --> 00:11:09,586
No, how could I?
I wouldn't touch your property, sir.

190
00:11:09,669 --> 00:11:10,962
[Chairman Ahn chuckles]

191
00:11:12,046 --> 00:11:13,089
[laughs]

192
00:11:13,173 --> 00:11:14,174
Right.

193
00:11:15,216 --> 00:11:17,135
You've always played it small,
haven't you?

194
00:11:18,761 --> 00:11:20,680
I once told him I'd take
his wife's kidney.

195
00:11:20,763 --> 00:11:23,474
[laughs]
He tried to hang himself.

196
00:11:23,558 --> 00:11:25,435
That's how freaked out he was.

197
00:11:26,144 --> 00:11:28,396
So I said I'd spare her life.

198
00:11:28,479 --> 00:11:32,483
And this man starts grovelling, begging.
"I'll do anything you say!"

199
00:11:33,651 --> 00:11:35,153
Just crying.

200
00:11:35,236 --> 00:11:37,322
[laughing]

201
00:11:37,405 --> 00:11:40,950
And that-that's why I like you,
Kim Jinman!

202
00:11:41,034 --> 00:11:42,493
You're still useful!

203
00:11:42,577 --> 00:11:45,580
[Chairman Ahn laughing]

204
00:11:48,333 --> 00:11:51,127
[Kang] Four five two one. No.

205
00:11:51,211 --> 00:11:53,087
How about this one here?

206
00:11:53,171 --> 00:11:55,131
JANGGAK TRADE INC.

207
00:11:55,215 --> 00:11:56,549
That's not it, either.

208
00:11:57,342 --> 00:11:59,510
Four three two oh.
Four three two oh.

209
00:11:59,594 --> 00:12:00,637
[grunts]

210
00:12:02,055 --> 00:12:04,974
[cell phone vibrating]

211
00:12:05,058 --> 00:12:07,477
Ah, shit.
What is it now?

212
00:12:10,438 --> 00:12:11,606
Yeah, what is it?

213
00:12:11,689 --> 00:12:14,609
[Jinman] <i>Are you looking for</i>
<i>a five two seven nine Santa Fe?</i>

214
00:12:14,692 --> 00:12:15,693
Yes.

215
00:12:16,402 --> 00:12:18,488
[Jinman] <i>I'm here, fucker. Here.</i>

216
00:12:18,571 --> 00:12:19,989
[clicks tongue]
Shit.

217
00:12:24,994 --> 00:12:27,747
Hey. I checked all
the cars here earlier today.

218
00:12:28,414 --> 00:12:29,415
It's not here.

219
00:12:31,167 --> 00:12:33,211
So then Park made you do this?

220
00:12:33,294 --> 00:12:35,338
No, Chairman Ahn.

221
00:12:35,421 --> 00:12:36,547
[groans]

222
00:12:36,631 --> 00:12:38,299
[Kang] Fuck, this is driving me crazy.

223
00:12:38,633 --> 00:12:39,801
[lip smacks]

224
00:12:41,135 --> 00:12:42,679
Hey, what's with that car, anyways?

225
00:12:43,263 --> 00:12:44,264
Is it Cha Yujin's?

226
00:12:44,764 --> 00:12:46,015
Well, I don't know.

227
00:12:49,310 --> 00:12:50,311
[Jinman] Hey.

228
00:12:51,562 --> 00:12:52,563
Thought you said you were done.

229
00:12:52,647 --> 00:12:55,233
You weren't gonna work for Geumsong,
so why are you?

230
00:12:55,900 --> 00:12:57,110
We lost Lee Dokyung.

231
00:12:58,653 --> 00:12:59,654
[both exhale sharply]

232
00:12:59,737 --> 00:13:00,738
[Jinman] Gosh.

233
00:13:00,822 --> 00:13:02,865
The department's already giving me hell
for this.

234
00:13:03,241 --> 00:13:04,450
Now the director, too.

235
00:13:05,118 --> 00:13:06,119
[clicks tongue]

236
00:13:08,997 --> 00:13:10,832
Just call it a night for now, yeah?

237
00:13:11,874 --> 00:13:15,211
My best guess is that there's a good
chance they got rid of it already.

238
00:13:15,295 --> 00:13:17,297
Probably dumped it in
a reservoir or something.

239
00:13:18,756 --> 00:13:22,093
Just tell Park that the car belonged
to Janggak Trading.

240
00:13:23,261 --> 00:13:25,096
[Kang] Right.
Yeah, that's a good call.

241
00:13:25,179 --> 00:13:26,180
Yeah.

242
00:13:28,850 --> 00:13:29,934
[exhales]

243
00:13:30,018 --> 00:13:33,021
[cell phone vibrating]

244
00:13:37,608 --> 00:13:38,609
You find it yet?

245
00:13:39,319 --> 00:13:41,237
[Kang] <i>Uh, no.</i>
<i>No, not exactly.</i>

246
00:13:42,780 --> 00:13:44,866
[inhales deeply]

247
00:13:46,617 --> 00:13:48,286
You're a stupid fuck.
You know that?

248
00:13:52,415 --> 00:13:55,585
Now wait. You see,
it's not a private vehicle.

249
00:13:55,668 --> 00:13:57,128
It belongs to a company.

250
00:13:57,962 --> 00:13:59,172
Fuck, which one?

251
00:13:59,630 --> 00:14:00,882
[Kang] <i>It's called Janggak Trading.</i>

252
00:14:01,591 --> 00:14:03,426
<i>It looks like a trading company,</i>

253
00:14:03,509 --> 00:14:05,553
<i>but they buy cheap Chinese cars</i>
<i>and sell them overseas.</i>

254
00:14:06,304 --> 00:14:07,472
Heo Donggu's company?

255
00:14:08,264 --> 00:14:09,891
[Kang] <i>Yeah.</i>
<i>Do you know it?</i>

256
00:14:11,893 --> 00:14:12,935
Good work.

257
00:14:13,936 --> 00:14:14,937
[phone beeps]

258
00:14:17,106 --> 00:14:20,109
[car engine rumbling]

259
00:14:20,735 --> 00:14:22,111
[Woogy] It's because my dad
suddenly collapsed.

260
00:14:22,195 --> 00:14:23,196
LETTER OF RESIGNATION

261
00:14:23,696 --> 00:14:26,574
I need to leave so I can help
him out on his farm.

262
00:14:27,116 --> 00:14:28,242
You're an orphan.

263
00:14:28,326 --> 00:14:29,535
Uh...

264
00:14:31,204 --> 00:14:32,955
...he's actually my uncle, not my dad.

265
00:14:33,039 --> 00:14:36,292
Do you think we're a real company
'cause we pay you a salary?

266
00:14:36,375 --> 00:14:38,503
You've always been able
to walk in as you please.

267
00:14:39,170 --> 00:14:41,464
I'll cut off your ear
if you wanna walk out, though.

268
00:14:42,882 --> 00:14:45,176
- Yes, I understand.
- You understand?

269
00:14:46,177 --> 00:14:47,512
Seriously?

270
00:14:47,595 --> 00:14:49,847
Just think it over.

271
00:14:49,931 --> 00:14:52,058
[Gitae] You won't make this kind
of money anywhere else.

272
00:14:52,141 --> 00:14:54,018
And you're one of our best.

273
00:14:55,520 --> 00:14:56,521
[door opens]

274
00:14:56,604 --> 00:14:58,648
Now get out.
Go on.

275
00:14:58,731 --> 00:15:01,400
Back to work, now!
Go, go, go, go.

276
00:15:05,154 --> 00:15:06,155
Hey.

277
00:15:11,119 --> 00:15:12,120
Sir.

278
00:15:15,414 --> 00:15:16,749
It was you.

279
00:15:16,833 --> 00:15:19,335
[both grunting]

280
00:15:20,920 --> 00:15:21,921
No, it wasn't!

281
00:15:24,132 --> 00:15:25,341
What do you mean?

282
00:15:27,468 --> 00:15:30,054
You're that kid whose ear
I almost took off, right?

283
00:15:31,806 --> 00:15:34,183
Uh, yes. That's correct.
[clears throat]

284
00:15:35,852 --> 00:15:36,936
It's still on there.

285
00:15:37,019 --> 00:15:39,522
Yes. It healed up well.

286
00:15:44,152 --> 00:15:45,278
Go on.

287
00:15:49,365 --> 00:15:52,076
[door creaking]

288
00:15:54,537 --> 00:15:55,580
[Gitae] Boss.

289
00:15:56,205 --> 00:15:57,498
Have a seat over here.

290
00:15:57,582 --> 00:15:59,167
[Gitae] Or should I call you President?

291
00:15:59,250 --> 00:16:01,043
You think I dragged myself here...

292
00:16:01,127 --> 00:16:02,211
[inhales]

293
00:16:02,295 --> 00:16:04,005
...just so I can sit in that chair again?

294
00:16:04,088 --> 00:16:07,425
That's true.
[laughs]

295
00:16:09,468 --> 00:16:11,012
Gitae, let's find the casket.

296
00:16:11,554 --> 00:16:13,055
Do you even know where it is?

297
00:16:14,932 --> 00:16:16,642
Well, come on, then!

298
00:16:16,726 --> 00:16:18,186
Let's go get it!

299
00:16:18,269 --> 00:16:20,938
And then, boom, your honor is back!

300
00:16:21,564 --> 00:16:22,690
[Gitae] We have to!

301
00:16:24,859 --> 00:16:28,738
[chuckling]

302
00:16:30,323 --> 00:16:31,782
[Woojin] It's Detective Kim.

303
00:16:31,866 --> 00:16:33,993
He thinks Janggak Trading is behind this.

304
00:16:34,785 --> 00:16:36,329
[Chairman Ahn] Janggak Trading?

305
00:16:36,412 --> 00:16:39,332
He told me you'd recognize
what that refers to.

306
00:16:40,166 --> 00:16:41,167
[grunts]

307
00:16:43,252 --> 00:16:44,545
[exhales]

308
00:16:46,589 --> 00:16:47,715
What's Janggak Trading?

309
00:16:48,466 --> 00:16:52,261
Oh, hello, sir.
Uh, it's Heo Donggu's company. Yeah.

310
00:16:52,345 --> 00:16:55,223
He was the man you kicked out, uh,
about ten years ago.

311
00:16:55,514 --> 00:16:57,725
- [Chairman Ahn] <i>Oh.</i>
- You remember, right?

312
00:16:57,808 --> 00:16:59,644
Okay, stay there.
Keep an eye on him.

313
00:17:01,270 --> 00:17:02,271
[phone beeps]

314
00:17:06,067 --> 00:17:08,903
Grab a few guys.
Head to Janggak Trading.

315
00:17:09,111 --> 00:17:10,112
When you get there,

316
00:17:10,196 --> 00:17:13,532
cut off Heo Donggu's other ear
and find the casket. Get moving.

317
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:15,660
Yes, sir.

318
00:17:15,743 --> 00:17:17,787
[Man] Ah, let's go.

319
00:17:17,870 --> 00:17:19,163
[Woogy] Janggak Trading?

320
00:17:19,872 --> 00:17:20,873
Mm-hmm.

321
00:17:22,124 --> 00:17:23,709
You know what those guys do, right?

322
00:17:23,793 --> 00:17:25,127
And you're buying a ferry ticket there?

323
00:17:25,211 --> 00:17:26,504
[Heeju] I know.

324
00:17:27,255 --> 00:17:28,422
I got the car there.

325
00:17:30,883 --> 00:17:32,552
And that's where I got the bullets, too.

326
00:17:33,427 --> 00:17:36,305
Ah, just give half the gold bars
to Dokyung and let him figure it out!

327
00:17:36,973 --> 00:17:39,600
That bastard is an expert at smuggling!
He'll know what to do!

328
00:17:43,229 --> 00:17:46,190
[Woogy] Heeju, seriously.
What are you thinking? Huh?

329
00:17:47,024 --> 00:17:48,025
We're not doing this.

330
00:17:48,568 --> 00:17:49,569
'Kay?

331
00:17:50,361 --> 00:17:53,656
You're giving him half the gold.
Buying a ferry ticket.

332
00:17:54,073 --> 00:17:55,658
[Woogy] You can't think like that anymore.

333
00:17:56,742 --> 00:17:58,578
We have to start looking out
for ourselves first.

334
00:18:02,373 --> 00:18:03,749
[exhales]
[silverware clatters]

335
00:18:07,044 --> 00:18:08,212
[exhales sharply]

336
00:18:14,302 --> 00:18:19,599
JG JANGGAK TRADE INC.
TRADING/ TRANSPORT/ LOGISTICS

337
00:18:27,231 --> 00:18:28,608
[car engine shuts off]

338
00:18:29,525 --> 00:18:30,526
Heeju.

339
00:18:37,074 --> 00:18:38,242
The gold bars.

340
00:18:39,327 --> 00:18:40,536
Why don't you just tell me where they are?

341
00:18:41,829 --> 00:18:43,289
It'd be just in case.

342
00:18:43,372 --> 00:18:46,500
If anything bad were to happen to you,
then don't you think I should know?

343
00:18:46,584 --> 00:18:47,877
Woogy.

344
00:18:47,960 --> 00:18:48,961
Why don't we do this?

345
00:18:49,754 --> 00:18:51,172
You could schedule an E-mail.

346
00:18:51,255 --> 00:18:53,341
Write it in there,
set it to send later.

347
00:18:53,424 --> 00:18:55,718
And if you come back safely,
you could just delete it.

348
00:18:57,178 --> 00:18:59,180
So then if I were to come back safely...

349
00:19:00,097 --> 00:19:01,474
...you would just kill me, right?

350
00:19:03,309 --> 00:19:05,061
Right, I see why you'd think that.

351
00:19:06,854 --> 00:19:08,397
Heeju, just be careful.

352
00:19:08,481 --> 00:19:10,024
- I really mean it, okay?
- Okay.

353
00:19:10,107 --> 00:19:12,568
Seriously, those guys can be crazy.
You need to watch your back.

354
00:19:18,366 --> 00:19:20,618
[inhales and exhales sharply]

355
00:19:27,333 --> 00:19:28,334
[Jinman] Kim Heeju?

356
00:19:35,216 --> 00:19:36,258
What is this?

357
00:19:38,010 --> 00:19:39,011
[Donggu] Anywhere?

358
00:19:41,055 --> 00:19:42,056
I see.

359
00:19:44,350 --> 00:19:48,020
There's a ferry leaving Mokcheon Port
in two days, if that works for you.

360
00:19:48,104 --> 00:19:49,647
What are you loading?

361
00:19:49,730 --> 00:19:51,232
There's one car.

362
00:19:52,149 --> 00:19:53,359
And one passenger.

363
00:19:53,442 --> 00:19:54,735
Stow away?

364
00:19:56,112 --> 00:19:57,279
[Donggu exhales]

365
00:19:58,447 --> 00:20:00,449
That's not a cheap thing to do, you know.

366
00:20:01,492 --> 00:20:04,787
Ten million, even 20 million won
just won't cut it.

367
00:20:04,870 --> 00:20:07,248
These days,
pocket change isn't enough.

368
00:20:12,002 --> 00:20:13,629
[Heeju] Take this up front.

369
00:20:13,713 --> 00:20:16,799
Once the transport is done,
I'll give you another one.

370
00:20:29,562 --> 00:20:32,898
All right, Park, you asshole.
Just show up already.

371
00:20:35,568 --> 00:20:36,610
[tires squeak]

372
00:20:36,694 --> 00:20:38,028
[car door opens]

373
00:20:40,197 --> 00:20:42,074
[cell phone trilling]

374
00:20:42,158 --> 00:20:43,325
[Jinman] Hey, yeah, Chief Cheon.

375
00:20:43,409 --> 00:20:45,077
Park is here right now.
You coming or what?

376
00:20:47,079 --> 00:20:48,873
[Woogy] Is that Park?

377
00:20:52,877 --> 00:20:54,837
HEEJU, DIRECTOR PARK IS HERE.

378
00:20:54,920 --> 00:20:56,756
[cell phone vibrates]
[Donggu exhales]

379
00:20:59,925 --> 00:21:01,343
GET OUT OF THERE RIGHT NOW.

380
00:21:02,428 --> 00:21:03,471
What?

381
00:21:05,014 --> 00:21:06,724
[gasping]

382
00:21:07,558 --> 00:21:11,479
[Donggu] Wait. Did you mess around
with Geumseong's stuff?

383
00:21:11,562 --> 00:21:15,941
You did! Come here! Come over here!
Quickly! Go, go, go, go, go!

384
00:21:16,025 --> 00:21:17,610
Hide here!

385
00:21:18,694 --> 00:21:21,697
In here! Okay. Inside this!
You need to get in. Okay.

386
00:21:21,781 --> 00:21:25,409
They won't find you in here. Here!
Don't even breathe! Okay?

387
00:21:25,493 --> 00:21:28,245
Don't make any noise!
You need to stay hidden in here!

388
00:21:28,329 --> 00:21:30,581
[Donggu breathing erratically]
Okay, good. Good.

389
00:21:30,664 --> 00:21:32,833
[heavy breathing]

390
00:21:33,834 --> 00:21:35,878
[bullets clattering on floor]
Oh, fuck me!

391
00:21:36,962 --> 00:21:38,714
Oh, gosh, I don't know!

392
00:21:38,798 --> 00:21:39,965
Ah!

393
00:21:41,175 --> 00:21:43,511
Hey there, Donggu.
It's been a while.

394
00:21:43,594 --> 00:21:46,138
[groaning]

395
00:21:46,847 --> 00:21:50,226
Hey, I think there was a misunderstanding,
right?

396
00:21:51,227 --> 00:21:52,144
[Donggu] What?

397
00:21:52,228 --> 00:21:54,730
[all shouting]
[glass shattering]

398
00:21:54,814 --> 00:21:57,650
[Donggu whimpering]

399
00:21:57,733 --> 00:21:59,318
You know I don't say things I don't mean.

400
00:21:59,401 --> 00:22:01,529
[Hocheol] Where'd you hide the casket?

401
00:22:02,071 --> 00:22:04,031
Tell me or I'll take your other ear.

402
00:22:04,114 --> 00:22:05,491
This is all a misunderstanding!

403
00:22:05,574 --> 00:22:08,619
This isn't a funeral home!
Why would you look for a casket here?

404
00:22:08,702 --> 00:22:10,287
Wait!

405
00:22:10,788 --> 00:22:13,791
[screaming]

406
00:22:16,043 --> 00:22:17,086
Stop it!

407
00:22:17,545 --> 00:22:20,256
[Doggu screaming]

408
00:22:24,552 --> 00:22:26,053
[tires squealing]

409
00:22:26,554 --> 00:22:28,472
What the actual fuck?

410
00:22:28,556 --> 00:22:29,557
[Woojin] Get up there!

411
00:22:33,853 --> 00:22:35,104
[coughs]

412
00:22:37,523 --> 00:22:39,149
[Donggu screaming]

413
00:22:39,233 --> 00:22:42,862
Ju! Ju Haran! Ah!
It's Ju Haran!

414
00:22:42,945 --> 00:22:44,321
It's Ju Haran!

415
00:22:44,405 --> 00:22:46,073
Who is Ju Haran?

416
00:22:46,156 --> 00:22:49,159
[Donggu screaming]

417
00:22:50,286 --> 00:22:51,912
[banging on door]

418
00:22:51,996 --> 00:22:53,122
[Gitae] Oh, shit!

419
00:22:53,205 --> 00:22:55,249
[banging continues]
Hey, boss!

420
00:22:55,332 --> 00:22:56,667
- [Gitae] Hurry!
- Fuck's sake!

421
00:22:56,750 --> 00:22:57,793
Ju Haran!
Who the fuck is she?

422
00:22:57,877 --> 00:22:59,128
I'm answering you!

423
00:22:59,211 --> 00:23:00,212
[Gitae shouts]

424
00:23:00,296 --> 00:23:02,131
[Gitae groans]

425
00:23:02,214 --> 00:23:04,133
[shouting]

426
00:23:05,342 --> 00:23:06,635
Fuck, it reeks in here.

427
00:23:06,719 --> 00:23:08,470
[Donggu wailing]

428
00:23:08,554 --> 00:23:09,638
What's this?

429
00:23:09,722 --> 00:23:12,224
This a Geumsong Alumni reunion?

430
00:23:12,308 --> 00:23:14,143
[Woojin laughs]

431
00:23:15,352 --> 00:23:16,896
Ah, come on.

432
00:23:17,521 --> 00:23:19,231
I'm really disappointed in you, Park.

433
00:23:20,024 --> 00:23:21,442
[Woojin] The chairman gave you a chance.

434
00:23:22,234 --> 00:23:23,319
But you know what you are?

435
00:23:24,403 --> 00:23:25,779
You're too old school.

436
00:23:26,322 --> 00:23:27,656
It's fucking pathetic.

437
00:23:28,908 --> 00:23:30,576
Both of you are.

438
00:23:30,659 --> 00:23:31,827
You thought you could take
the chairman's casket

439
00:23:31,911 --> 00:23:33,203
and just get away with it?

440
00:23:33,287 --> 00:23:34,997
It was a rhetorical question, you fuck.

441
00:23:35,581 --> 00:23:37,708
[Woojin] 'Kay, last chance.

442
00:23:38,417 --> 00:23:40,210
Who'd like to be the first to talk?

443
00:23:40,294 --> 00:23:42,087
Where's the casket?

444
00:23:42,171 --> 00:23:43,714
Okay, listen. It's not like that.

445
00:23:43,797 --> 00:23:45,925
The boss and I came here for Donggu.

446
00:23:46,008 --> 00:23:47,635
- He's the one who stole the casket.
- [Donggu] Bullshit!

447
00:23:47,718 --> 00:23:49,845
- He took it.
- I don't fucking have it, you liar!

448
00:23:50,596 --> 00:23:52,848
[whimpers]
Just, fuck.

449
00:23:52,932 --> 00:23:54,642
Just give me a second to explain!

450
00:23:54,725 --> 00:23:56,018
[Donggu] That car?

451
00:23:56,101 --> 00:23:59,229
A week ago a lady called Ju Haran came by
and bought it from me.

452
00:23:59,313 --> 00:24:01,065
- Ju Haran, huh?
- [Donggu] Fuck, how many times

453
00:24:01,148 --> 00:24:03,317
do I have to tell you?
How do I explain this?

454
00:24:03,400 --> 00:24:05,569
I have no idea, really!
I don't know!

455
00:24:05,653 --> 00:24:07,321
I've never once seen the casket!

456
00:24:07,404 --> 00:24:09,698
[Donggu] All I did was to sell a car
to this woman named Ju Haran.

457
00:24:09,782 --> 00:24:12,534
You don't believe me?
Let me show you the contract she signed!

458
00:24:13,243 --> 00:24:14,244
Where is it?

459
00:24:15,454 --> 00:24:16,622
I'll get it!

460
00:24:22,461 --> 00:24:24,254
[footsteps stomping]

461
00:24:24,838 --> 00:24:26,882
It's here!
This one!

462
00:24:27,424 --> 00:24:30,886
[whimpering]

463
00:24:31,845 --> 00:24:33,389
What are you doing?

464
00:24:36,517 --> 00:24:37,559
[Gitae] Boss.

465
00:24:37,643 --> 00:24:39,353
Hand it over!

466
00:24:39,436 --> 00:24:41,438
[Gitae] They think we're the ones
who stole the casket!

467
00:24:43,524 --> 00:24:44,942
I'd like to see it now.

468
00:24:50,990 --> 00:24:53,242
Come and get it, you motherfucker.

469
00:24:53,325 --> 00:24:56,745
Wow. You're fucking stubborn.

470
00:24:58,122 --> 00:24:59,415
Keep him alive, okay?

471
00:25:01,125 --> 00:25:02,751
Wait!
[gasps]

472
00:25:06,797 --> 00:25:09,800
[blows landing]
[All grunting]

473
00:25:18,350 --> 00:25:21,353
[blade slicing]
[Henchman screaming]

474
00:25:29,820 --> 00:25:30,821
[blow lands]

475
00:25:33,532 --> 00:25:35,159
[glass shatters]

476
00:25:45,919 --> 00:25:48,505
[both groaning]

477
00:25:54,803 --> 00:25:57,389
[gunshot]
[groaning]

478
00:25:57,473 --> 00:25:58,474
[labored breathing]

479
00:25:58,557 --> 00:25:59,850
[gasps]

480
00:25:59,933 --> 00:26:01,602
[all breathing heavily]

481
00:26:01,685 --> 00:26:02,978
You fucking asshole!

482
00:26:03,771 --> 00:26:05,898
[glass shattering]

483
00:26:05,981 --> 00:26:07,441
[groans]

484
00:26:09,151 --> 00:26:10,736
Oh, fuck.

485
00:26:10,819 --> 00:26:13,572
[both grunting]

486
00:26:14,073 --> 00:26:16,158
[banging and grunting]

487
00:26:20,704 --> 00:26:21,789
[glass shatters]

488
00:26:24,083 --> 00:26:25,834
[panicked breathing]

489
00:26:25,918 --> 00:26:28,629
[both grunting]

490
00:26:30,047 --> 00:26:32,216
[pained groaning]

491
00:26:32,299 --> 00:26:33,634
Wait, wait, wait!

492
00:26:34,384 --> 00:26:37,930
Okay, okay! You win, Park!
You win, Park! You win, Park, okay?

493
00:26:38,013 --> 00:26:40,057
Just a sec.
Let's not do this.

494
00:26:40,140 --> 00:26:41,892
We'll let you go if you just apologize.

495
00:26:41,975 --> 00:26:43,519
[Woojin] We can just bring
any old document and-

496
00:26:43,602 --> 00:26:46,772
[screaming]
Shit, okay, never mind! I'm sorry, okay?

497
00:26:46,855 --> 00:26:48,440
Let's just find the casket!

498
00:26:48,524 --> 00:26:50,818
Then the Chairman'll spare your life,
right? Okay?

499
00:26:51,360 --> 00:26:52,945
I can explain everything.

500
00:26:53,028 --> 00:26:54,321
[Woojin screaming]

501
00:26:54,863 --> 00:26:55,906
Boss!

502
00:26:55,989 --> 00:26:57,407
[Gitae] Have you lost your mind?

503
00:26:57,491 --> 00:26:59,243
[Woojin groans]

504
00:26:59,326 --> 00:27:01,662
Shit. Fuck!

505
00:27:03,330 --> 00:27:04,498
[groaning]

506
00:27:04,998 --> 00:27:07,960
[pained groans]

507
00:27:08,043 --> 00:27:10,087
You wanna save him,
you better take him to the hospital.

508
00:27:10,170 --> 00:27:12,923
- [Hocheol grunts]
- [gagging]

509
00:27:15,425 --> 00:27:16,718
Boss!

510
00:27:16,802 --> 00:27:18,220
Oh, man.

511
00:27:18,804 --> 00:27:20,722
[door creaking]

512
00:27:20,806 --> 00:27:22,724
[Jinman] What the-
is Park running away?

513
00:27:22,808 --> 00:27:25,185
Shit. Shit.

514
00:27:25,727 --> 00:27:27,020
This fucking...

515
00:27:27,104 --> 00:27:29,356
[grunting]

516
00:27:31,567 --> 00:27:34,570
[car engine turns over]

517
00:27:41,785 --> 00:27:43,120
Oh, sh-

518
00:27:51,753 --> 00:27:54,256
What the fuck is even going on?

519
00:27:54,339 --> 00:27:57,301
Hey, what happened here?
Heo Donggu, what just happened?

520
00:27:57,384 --> 00:27:58,552
[Gitae] Oh, fuck!

521
00:27:58,635 --> 00:28:01,013
What do you think happened?
Just take a look around!

522
00:28:01,096 --> 00:28:03,223
Ju Haran, I'm looking for her.
Have you seen her?

523
00:28:03,307 --> 00:28:06,059
Ju Haran? Well, I dunno.
Look at this place. I dunno.

524
00:28:06,143 --> 00:28:08,687
I saw her walk in here with my own eyes,
you asshole!

525
00:28:08,770 --> 00:28:10,647
[Donggu] What are you talking about?
Nobody came here!

526
00:28:10,731 --> 00:28:12,149
Can't you see this mess?

527
00:28:12,232 --> 00:28:14,318
You motherfucker! If you're lying to me,
I swear I'll fucking kill you.

528
00:28:14,401 --> 00:28:16,820
I'm not lying! Why would I?
I'm not lying to you! I swear!

529
00:28:16,904 --> 00:28:17,905
[Gitae] Detective Kim!

530
00:28:17,988 --> 00:28:19,281
Over here!

531
00:28:19,823 --> 00:28:21,074
Help me out!

532
00:28:21,158 --> 00:28:22,743
- [Gitae] Please, hurry!
- This fucking...

533
00:28:22,826 --> 00:28:24,912
[Gitae] Detective Kim!
Come on, hurry up!

534
00:28:24,995 --> 00:28:27,497
- Get over here! Come on, hurry!
- What happened to Chief Cheon?

535
00:28:27,581 --> 00:28:28,790
[Gitae] Come on, get over here!

536
00:28:28,874 --> 00:28:30,876
[both speaking at once]

537
00:28:30,959 --> 00:28:32,210
[Jinman] Here we go.

538
00:28:33,045 --> 00:28:34,963
Get him out of here.

539
00:28:35,047 --> 00:28:36,214
- Stay with us, Chief Cheon!
- Shit.

540
00:28:36,298 --> 00:28:39,343
If you die, we'll all end up dead!
Come on, we gotta move!

541
00:28:39,426 --> 00:28:41,303
[Cheon coughing]

542
00:28:42,930 --> 00:28:44,890
Come on!

543
00:28:45,766 --> 00:28:47,142
Shit.

544
00:28:47,225 --> 00:28:48,810
[cell phone buzzing]
Oh!

545
00:28:49,227 --> 00:28:50,270
Hello? Heeju?

546
00:28:50,812 --> 00:28:52,397
Tell me what the fuck
is goin' on in there!

547
00:28:52,481 --> 00:28:54,232
[Heeju] <i>Woogy, you have to run.</i>

548
00:28:54,316 --> 00:28:56,234
<i>Detective Kim is heading your way.</i>

549
00:28:56,944 --> 00:28:58,195
What are you gonna-
[phone beeps]

550
00:28:58,278 --> 00:28:59,279
Hello?

551
00:29:00,280 --> 00:29:01,281
Shit.

552
00:29:01,365 --> 00:29:04,076
[Gitae] Chief Cheon!
Please, please, don't die!

553
00:29:04,743 --> 00:29:06,787
- Please don't die!
- [grunts]

554
00:29:06,870 --> 00:29:08,580
[Gitae] We're in big trouble.

555
00:29:11,667 --> 00:29:13,001
[Donggu] No!

556
00:29:13,794 --> 00:29:14,920
They're all gone.

557
00:29:15,003 --> 00:29:16,838
[both breathing heavily]

558
00:29:18,924 --> 00:29:20,509
You can come out now.

559
00:29:22,302 --> 00:29:24,388
[footsteps on broken glass]

560
00:29:32,187 --> 00:29:33,188
[Donggu] Listen.

561
00:29:33,772 --> 00:29:34,940
Let's make a deal.

562
00:29:36,566 --> 00:29:38,819
Those men,
the ones that were here,

563
00:29:38,902 --> 00:29:40,278
I'm not like them at all.

564
00:29:41,113 --> 00:29:42,781
[Donggu] And I'm not that greedy, either.

565
00:29:43,699 --> 00:29:46,201
I'm not ambitious.

566
00:29:46,284 --> 00:29:48,662
All I'd like is to live a long life.

567
00:29:49,413 --> 00:29:53,458
And drugs, I'm out of that business.
I cut all connections ten years ago!

568
00:29:53,542 --> 00:29:54,918
I'm my own man now.

569
00:29:55,752 --> 00:29:57,004
The casket...

570
00:29:58,255 --> 00:30:01,216
Listen, shit, I really don't care
about it at all.

571
00:30:02,134 --> 00:30:04,428
Why else would I hide you in that cabinet?

572
00:30:04,511 --> 00:30:07,973
I hid you and I didn't tell those guys
that you're actually Kim Heeju,

573
00:30:08,056 --> 00:30:09,307
not Ju Haran.

574
00:30:11,810 --> 00:30:13,228
So what do you want from me?

575
00:30:15,731 --> 00:30:17,065
The transport fee.

576
00:30:18,275 --> 00:30:19,568
Ten gold bars.

577
00:30:20,235 --> 00:30:21,361
One billion won?

578
00:30:23,321 --> 00:30:24,990
We can negotiate, too.

579
00:30:25,073 --> 00:30:27,909
And also, uh,
after sales service?

580
00:30:27,993 --> 00:30:30,370
I'll take full responsibility
for everything right up till the end!

581
00:30:30,454 --> 00:30:31,455
I swear it!

582
00:30:33,206 --> 00:30:34,374
[Donggu] I mean it.

583
00:30:35,000 --> 00:30:36,543
[car alarm beeps]

584
00:30:36,626 --> 00:30:39,337
<i>[Donggu inhales]</i>
<i>Look, that car over there.</i>

585
00:30:39,838 --> 00:30:42,841
<i>It's collateral I got yesterday.</i>
<i>You can take it. It's on me.</i>

586
00:30:43,759 --> 00:30:45,260
<i>I haven't even taken it to the garage yet.</i>

587
00:30:45,343 --> 00:30:48,847
<i>Feel free to drive it as much as you want,</i>
<i>and then get rid of it.</i>

588
00:30:48,930 --> 00:30:51,725
[car engine revving]

589
00:31:02,652 --> 00:31:04,196
You can rest now.

590
00:31:07,407 --> 00:31:09,910
[♪ tense music]

591
00:31:09,993 --> 00:31:12,579
No need to make a big deal out of it.
Just have him cremated.

592
00:31:12,662 --> 00:31:13,663
Yes, sir.

593
00:31:14,206 --> 00:31:16,666
- Let Kim Jinman take care of the rest.
- Yes, sir.

594
00:31:17,084 --> 00:31:18,585
Have you found Park Hocheol yet?

595
00:31:19,544 --> 00:31:20,670
No.

596
00:31:20,754 --> 00:31:21,755
What?

597
00:31:23,173 --> 00:31:26,093
Get out there and find him immediately
before I rip each and every one of you

598
00:31:26,176 --> 00:31:27,511
- into fucking pieces!
- Right away.

599
00:31:36,311 --> 00:31:37,938
[Chairman Ahn] Are you doing okay, Ko?

600
00:31:38,605 --> 00:31:39,773
Yes, I'm okay, sir.

601
00:31:41,316 --> 00:31:43,568
[Chairman Ahn] Did you really not know
that Park had a lead?

602
00:31:44,486 --> 00:31:46,071
On the casket?

603
00:31:46,571 --> 00:31:50,325
[Jinman] Well, I hadn't really considered
that he would still be after it, sir.

604
00:31:50,408 --> 00:31:54,621
Honestly, uh,
I thought he'd gone back to Yes Money

605
00:31:54,704 --> 00:31:56,623
- and just given up on it.
- Whatever.

606
00:31:56,706 --> 00:31:59,167
Now bring me either Lee Dokyung
or Ju Haran.

607
00:31:59,251 --> 00:32:02,629
You're supposed to be the expert on this.
Just do your job.

608
00:32:02,712 --> 00:32:04,548
Then I'll get 'em to talk.

609
00:32:05,340 --> 00:32:06,967
Let's stick to what we're good at.

610
00:32:07,759 --> 00:32:08,760
Yes, sir.

611
00:32:09,344 --> 00:32:13,181
But if Park Hocheol finds that girl
or the casket before you do...

612
00:32:14,307 --> 00:32:16,643
...you can kiss one of your ears goodbye.

613
00:32:16,726 --> 00:32:17,894
[Jinman grunts]

614
00:32:24,693 --> 00:32:27,696
HAENGBOK PAWNSHOP

615
00:32:32,659 --> 00:32:35,662
[door rattling]

616
00:32:39,875 --> 00:32:42,878
[distant clocks quietly ticking]

617
00:32:52,095 --> 00:32:53,471
[door creaks]

618
00:33:03,899 --> 00:33:06,067
[grunts]

619
00:33:06,151 --> 00:33:07,152
[clunks]

620
00:33:09,988 --> 00:33:12,115
[gold bars scraping]

621
00:33:18,788 --> 00:33:21,791
[♪ dramatic music]

622
00:33:32,928 --> 00:33:34,512
[exhales]

623
00:33:46,233 --> 00:33:47,651
[cell phone vibrating]

624
00:33:47,984 --> 00:33:51,112
INCOMING CALL
SUNOK

625
00:33:52,489 --> 00:33:53,865
[vibrating continues]

626
00:33:53,949 --> 00:33:54,991
[phone clicks]

627
00:33:56,243 --> 00:33:57,244
Hello?

628
00:33:58,453 --> 00:33:59,871
[Sunok] <i>Can I see you for a bit?</i>

629
00:34:03,083 --> 00:34:04,084
Now?

630
00:34:06,044 --> 00:34:07,254
Uh...

631
00:34:08,713 --> 00:34:09,798
Okay.

632
00:34:10,840 --> 00:34:11,841
Be right there.

633
00:34:14,386 --> 00:34:15,387
[phone beeps]

634
00:34:17,847 --> 00:34:19,891
Ah, dammit.

635
00:34:19,975 --> 00:34:22,978
[car engine revving]

636
00:34:38,410 --> 00:34:41,413
[inhales on cigarette]

637
00:34:46,167 --> 00:34:50,797
VEHICLE TRANSFER CERTIFICATE
JU HARAN

638
00:34:50,880 --> 00:34:52,007
Ju Haran.

639
00:34:52,090 --> 00:34:54,551
I've heard that name before.
Fuck.

640
00:34:56,428 --> 00:34:57,637
Dammit.

641
00:34:59,306 --> 00:35:00,515
[exhales]

642
00:35:02,892 --> 00:35:04,686
That's the bitch I killed.

643
00:35:07,939 --> 00:35:08,940
[exhales]

644
00:35:10,734 --> 00:35:12,068
[chuckles]

645
00:35:12,527 --> 00:35:19,534
YES MONEY

646
00:35:25,582 --> 00:35:26,958
[inhales]

647
00:35:36,051 --> 00:35:38,386
[knocking on door]
[Moonsu] Boss.

648
00:35:38,470 --> 00:35:40,013
- Boss.
- [Gitae] What?

649
00:35:40,096 --> 00:35:42,015
Did you see a ghost or something?

650
00:35:42,098 --> 00:35:44,225
[all gasping]

651
00:35:45,101 --> 00:35:46,227
[door closes]

652
00:35:46,895 --> 00:35:47,979
Sir, what're...

653
00:35:50,398 --> 00:35:52,317
Nobody saw anything,
so keep your mouth shut.

654
00:35:53,568 --> 00:35:55,153
And no makin' any phone calls!

655
00:35:55,236 --> 00:35:56,696
- [Both] Yes, sir.
- [Gitae] Now get the fuck out.

656
00:35:56,780 --> 00:35:57,864
Shut the door.

657
00:35:58,865 --> 00:36:00,575
[Gitae exhales]
Why'd you come here?

658
00:36:01,868 --> 00:36:03,286
[door closes]

659
00:36:03,370 --> 00:36:04,579
You know you're being hunted.

660
00:36:04,663 --> 00:36:06,998
The Geumseong guys
are all over looking for you.

661
00:36:07,082 --> 00:36:08,750
[exhales]

662
00:36:08,833 --> 00:36:10,168
Where else should I go?

663
00:36:11,211 --> 00:36:12,504
This here is my turf.

664
00:36:13,380 --> 00:36:14,923
You know Chief Cheon died, right?

665
00:36:15,382 --> 00:36:16,466
He was cremated.

666
00:36:17,175 --> 00:36:19,010
- Yeah?
- Leave Jeongsan.

667
00:36:19,761 --> 00:36:21,721
Chairman Ahn will find out you were here.

668
00:36:21,805 --> 00:36:23,348
And then he'll murder us both.

669
00:36:24,099 --> 00:36:25,558
[exhales]

670
00:36:25,642 --> 00:36:26,893
Where's Ju Haran?

671
00:36:29,479 --> 00:36:30,480
I don't know.

672
00:36:32,232 --> 00:36:34,025
The Geumseong guys must be looking
for her.

673
00:36:35,402 --> 00:36:36,403
Gitae.

674
00:36:38,738 --> 00:36:40,532
Do you know who Ju Haran is?

675
00:36:41,950 --> 00:36:42,992
No, who?

676
00:36:43,493 --> 00:36:44,828
You know Gu Jaok, right?

677
00:36:45,662 --> 00:36:47,789
She's the largest backer in Gangwon.

678
00:36:49,082 --> 00:36:52,711
There's no one in Jeongsan who hasn't
set foot on land that old lady owns.

679
00:36:53,545 --> 00:36:55,630
Ju Haran is her granddaughter.

680
00:36:55,714 --> 00:36:56,715
What?

681
00:36:57,549 --> 00:36:58,717
Around a year ago...

682
00:36:59,676 --> 00:37:03,596
...Chairman Ahn wanted to buy the 2%
of Gu's stake in Gold Land.

683
00:37:05,432 --> 00:37:08,393
That would have made him Gold Land's
biggest shareholder.

684
00:37:08,893 --> 00:37:10,854
However, Ms. Gu knew what he was doing...

685
00:37:12,272 --> 00:37:14,315
...and she refused to hand over her stake.

686
00:37:15,066 --> 00:37:17,569
So I found her collateral,
and took it from her.

687
00:37:19,154 --> 00:37:20,155
Ju Haran.

688
00:37:20,989 --> 00:37:22,615
[Gitae] So what's going on?

689
00:37:23,116 --> 00:37:27,787
If Ju is her granddaughter,
she took the casket...

690
00:37:28,913 --> 00:37:31,082
...is Ms. Gu the one behind all this?

691
00:37:31,166 --> 00:37:33,126
No, that's not it.

692
00:37:35,378 --> 00:37:36,838
Ju Haran's already dead.

693
00:37:37,839 --> 00:37:39,007
I killed her.

694
00:37:40,008 --> 00:37:42,802
Mr. Jin took care of the body
and dumped it at the farm.

695
00:37:43,470 --> 00:37:46,473
Well then, who's the Ju Haran
with the casket now?

696
00:37:46,556 --> 00:37:48,183
She's a fake.

697
00:37:48,266 --> 00:37:50,018
[Hocheol] Someone's pretending
to be Ju Haran,

698
00:37:50,101 --> 00:37:51,770
and they've even been using her ID.

699
00:37:53,021 --> 00:37:54,481
But as you probably know...

700
00:37:55,774 --> 00:37:57,984
...we're supposed to keep hold
of every ID card.

701
00:37:58,860 --> 00:38:00,403
[inhales]

702
00:38:01,154 --> 00:38:03,907
That's right. ID card.

703
00:38:06,868 --> 00:38:07,869
[Gitae] Let's see.

704
00:38:07,952 --> 00:38:09,329
Fuck.

705
00:38:09,412 --> 00:38:10,747
Where is it?

706
00:38:20,131 --> 00:38:22,425
[breathing heavily]

707
00:38:22,967 --> 00:38:23,968
[Gitae] What's this?

708
00:38:27,096 --> 00:38:28,973
Her ID card is missing.

709
00:38:32,811 --> 00:38:34,896
[stammering]
I didn't do it!

710
00:38:35,772 --> 00:38:36,981
[Hocheol] Then who was it?

711
00:38:37,816 --> 00:38:39,025
Who has access to them?

712
00:38:42,779 --> 00:38:44,030
Someone with access.

713
00:38:44,113 --> 00:38:45,365
Who's here alone.

714
00:38:46,157 --> 00:38:47,158
Woogy.

715
00:38:47,992 --> 00:38:50,370
[Gitae] That fucking punk that handles
the office supplies and the cleaning,

716
00:38:50,453 --> 00:38:51,746
all that stuff.

717
00:38:51,830 --> 00:38:53,498
Where's that bastard now?

718
00:38:53,581 --> 00:38:55,583
He tried to leave the company recently.

719
00:38:56,459 --> 00:38:57,627
That piece of shit.

720
00:38:59,087 --> 00:39:00,129
Hey, Moonsu!

721
00:39:01,005 --> 00:39:02,924
- Yes, Boss?
- [Gitae] You work with Woogy, right?

722
00:39:03,174 --> 00:39:04,175
Yes.

723
00:39:04,259 --> 00:39:06,761
Go find him!
Find him and bring him here!

724
00:39:06,845 --> 00:39:08,221
But Woogy already quit.

725
00:39:08,721 --> 00:39:10,014
Yeah, no shit, you dumb ass!

726
00:39:10,098 --> 00:39:11,975
So fucking bring him to me right now!

727
00:39:12,308 --> 00:39:13,309
Yes, right away.

728
00:39:13,393 --> 00:39:14,978
[door creaks]

729
00:39:15,895 --> 00:39:18,273
[distant footsteps stomping away]

730
00:39:18,356 --> 00:39:21,067
So, what are you gonna do now, Boss?

731
00:39:21,150 --> 00:39:22,402
[Hocheol] What about you?

732
00:39:22,485 --> 00:39:23,903
What are you gonna do?

733
00:39:25,238 --> 00:39:27,073
I'm already tracking down
the fake Ju Haran

734
00:39:27,156 --> 00:39:28,491
and I'm close to finding her.

735
00:39:30,201 --> 00:39:33,246
You can go get that thief
who stole her ID card from us.

736
00:39:33,329 --> 00:39:35,248
After that, we find the casket.

737
00:39:35,707 --> 00:39:36,708
[Gitae] So then...

738
00:39:37,292 --> 00:39:41,129
Wait a sec. Find the casket.
I know that's what you want.

739
00:39:42,005 --> 00:39:44,299
But we'll need to double cross Geumseong
for it.

740
00:39:45,133 --> 00:39:46,885
Do you really think that's worth it?

741
00:39:49,137 --> 00:39:50,930
You don't even know what's inside of it,
do you?

742
00:39:51,014 --> 00:39:52,724
Obviously drugs!

743
00:39:52,807 --> 00:39:54,809
They're a pain in the ass to sell,
ya know?

744
00:39:55,310 --> 00:39:56,936
Gold bars.

745
00:39:58,521 --> 00:39:59,731
One ton.

746
00:40:01,316 --> 00:40:03,526
It's worth 150 billion won.

747
00:40:09,115 --> 00:40:11,492
Now do you get why I turned against Ahn?

748
00:40:13,119 --> 00:40:14,579
[exhales]

749
00:40:16,080 --> 00:40:17,081
But...

750
00:40:19,000 --> 00:40:22,503
...if it's that kind of money,
Chairman Ahn's not just gonna give up.

751
00:40:23,379 --> 00:40:26,799
If he loses that casket,
he'll end up in one of his own.

752
00:40:26,883 --> 00:40:28,843
[Hocheol] That's the investment money
from Cambodia

753
00:40:28,927 --> 00:40:30,720
for the joint Gold Resort development.

754
00:40:31,471 --> 00:40:35,058
If the deal falls through
and they don't get their principal back...

755
00:40:37,226 --> 00:40:38,853
...they're not just gonna
let him walk away.

756
00:40:40,605 --> 00:40:42,231
[Hocheol] Now, you need to decide.

757
00:40:45,401 --> 00:40:46,945
Whose side are you on?

758
00:40:50,031 --> 00:40:51,491
'Cause I'm all in.

759
00:40:52,241 --> 00:40:54,202
[inhales deeply]

760
00:40:54,285 --> 00:40:55,870
[exhales]

761
00:40:55,954 --> 00:40:58,289
[cigarette rubbing on ashtray]

762
00:41:20,186 --> 00:41:21,270
You're here.

763
00:41:21,354 --> 00:41:22,480
Yeah.

764
00:41:26,484 --> 00:41:28,111
That a side effect of the chemo?

765
00:41:29,487 --> 00:41:31,447
[Jinman] Well, at least
you're getting treatment.

766
00:41:31,531 --> 00:41:32,699
You'll be good soon.

767
00:41:35,535 --> 00:41:36,911
Tomorrow's my surgery.

768
00:41:37,870 --> 00:41:39,706
Really? That's good to hear.

769
00:41:40,623 --> 00:41:41,791
I hope it goes well.

770
00:41:43,126 --> 00:41:44,377
[Jinman] Better sooner than later.

771
00:41:48,172 --> 00:41:49,424
Will your niece be here?

772
00:41:49,507 --> 00:41:50,508
No.

773
00:41:54,345 --> 00:41:56,347
I called because I wanted
to see your face.

774
00:41:58,516 --> 00:42:00,601
Might be the last time I see you.

775
00:42:01,227 --> 00:42:03,896
What are you talking about?
Come on.

776
00:42:04,897 --> 00:42:05,898
Don't know.

777
00:42:07,525 --> 00:42:08,568
[grunts]

778
00:42:08,651 --> 00:42:10,111
I just have a feeling it might.

779
00:42:10,820 --> 00:42:12,280
[Jinman] You're talking nonsense now.

780
00:42:12,905 --> 00:42:13,990
Jeez.

781
00:42:14,073 --> 00:42:15,074
[clicks tongue]

782
00:42:16,451 --> 00:42:17,577
Could...

783
00:42:17,660 --> 00:42:18,911
[inhales]

784
00:42:18,995 --> 00:42:21,414
Could you give me a bath tonight?

785
00:42:22,206 --> 00:42:23,374
A bath?

786
00:42:24,250 --> 00:42:25,251
Mm-hmm.

787
00:42:27,170 --> 00:42:28,379
You remember...

788
00:42:30,590 --> 00:42:32,842
...when we were young
and I'd come home drunk...

789
00:42:33,468 --> 00:42:34,886
...you would help wash me up?

790
00:42:34,969 --> 00:42:36,012
[chuckles]

791
00:42:38,389 --> 00:42:39,766
I did?

792
00:42:40,725 --> 00:42:41,976
If I'm going to die...

793
00:42:44,353 --> 00:42:46,355
...I wanna die with some grace.

794
00:42:48,775 --> 00:42:51,778
[water running]

795
00:42:55,031 --> 00:42:56,115
[Sunok] Looking back...

796
00:42:57,867 --> 00:43:00,119
...that really was the spring time
of my life.

797
00:43:03,331 --> 00:43:04,582
Living in Namju.

798
00:43:07,585 --> 00:43:08,711
With you.

799
00:43:08,795 --> 00:43:10,922
The two of us in that little mining town.

800
00:43:12,673 --> 00:43:14,509
[water wringing from hair]

801
00:43:14,592 --> 00:43:15,593
Yeah.

802
00:43:16,928 --> 00:43:18,638
I barely remember those days.

803
00:43:23,768 --> 00:43:25,603
I resented you afterward.

804
00:43:26,813 --> 00:43:27,897
For quite a while.

805
00:43:31,692 --> 00:43:34,487
I always wished that you
hadn't disappeared so suddenly.

806
00:43:37,115 --> 00:43:38,449
Even if I stayed...

807
00:43:43,663 --> 00:43:45,123
[Jinman] Fucking hell.

808
00:43:45,206 --> 00:43:46,499
What kind of a man were you with?

809
00:43:46,582 --> 00:43:47,583
Fuck.

810
00:43:48,292 --> 00:43:49,544
[exhales]

811
00:43:49,627 --> 00:43:52,755
That's what happens when you're nothing
but bad luck.

812
00:43:53,464 --> 00:43:54,715
[clicks tongue]

813
00:43:54,799 --> 00:43:55,883
[Sunok] But back then...

814
00:43:56,801 --> 00:43:58,803
...it really was all I could do
to survive.

815
00:44:01,514 --> 00:44:03,599
The years I spent living with that man...

816
00:44:06,144 --> 00:44:07,603
...they were nothing but hell.

817
00:44:10,898 --> 00:44:13,484
It felt like it wouldn't end until one
of us died.

818
00:44:14,986 --> 00:44:16,028
[Sunok] But...

819
00:44:17,613 --> 00:44:19,323
...the thought of being
the first to die...

820
00:44:23,286 --> 00:44:24,579
...that seemed too unfair.

821
00:44:26,622 --> 00:44:27,748
[exhales]

822
00:44:27,832 --> 00:44:28,833
[Sunok] So then...

823
00:44:29,625 --> 00:44:30,793
...I killed him.

824
00:44:30,877 --> 00:44:32,044
[inhales]

825
00:44:33,880 --> 00:44:36,340
Han Cheoljung, that bastard.

826
00:44:38,801 --> 00:44:40,052
I killed him.

827
00:45:00,698 --> 00:45:01,908
[Jinman clears throat]

828
00:45:19,675 --> 00:45:21,093
[Jinman] I'll cut it now.

829
00:45:32,188 --> 00:45:34,565
[Jinman] You have a nice head shape.
Don't worry.

830
00:45:35,650 --> 00:45:38,861
There was that bald singer from the UK.
You used to like her, didn't you?

831
00:45:38,945 --> 00:45:41,572
You kind of look like her.
You look pretty.

832
00:45:41,656 --> 00:45:42,823
Not bad, right?

833
00:45:43,366 --> 00:45:44,617
[groans]

834
00:45:45,117 --> 00:45:46,202
[exhales]

835
00:45:55,419 --> 00:45:56,963
Heeju isn't my niece.

836
00:45:59,090 --> 00:46:00,549
She's my daughter.

837
00:46:00,633 --> 00:46:01,634
What?

838
00:46:06,597 --> 00:46:08,057
And you're her father.

839
00:46:10,017 --> 00:46:11,269
[Sunok] After you left...

840
00:46:12,144 --> 00:46:14,272
...I found out that I was pregnant.

841
00:46:16,732 --> 00:46:18,985
The house where we lived together
in Namju...

842
00:46:20,486 --> 00:46:21,904
...that's where Heeju was born.

843
00:46:23,155 --> 00:46:25,283
[chuckles]

844
00:46:26,117 --> 00:46:27,910
You're kidding, right?

845
00:46:28,536 --> 00:46:29,537
It's a joke.

846
00:46:31,163 --> 00:46:32,415
[Jinman] That doesn't make any sense.

847
00:46:33,249 --> 00:46:35,668
I was going to keep it
a secret until I died.

848
00:46:36,836 --> 00:46:39,046
I didn't think I'd see you again.

849
00:46:39,880 --> 00:46:40,965
Okay, then.

850
00:46:41,048 --> 00:46:42,341
Why say all of this now?

851
00:46:43,968 --> 00:46:44,969
Jinman.

852
00:46:46,512 --> 00:46:48,514
[grunting]

853
00:46:51,058 --> 00:46:52,059
Heeju...

854
00:46:53,185 --> 00:46:56,022
I think she's unhappy nowadays.

855
00:46:57,606 --> 00:46:59,150
She's in trouble.

856
00:47:00,693 --> 00:47:02,153
And it's all because of me, I know.

857
00:47:03,529 --> 00:47:06,198
I just can't be buried with all
of that guilt.

858
00:47:06,949 --> 00:47:09,118
[Sunok] Not when it was me
who made her that way.

859
00:47:10,161 --> 00:47:12,371
I've always told her she
was a luckless brat...

860
00:47:13,497 --> 00:47:15,333
...born from a luckless bitch.

861
00:47:17,626 --> 00:47:18,627
So could you...

862
00:47:19,670 --> 00:47:21,297
...could you please take care of her?

863
00:47:23,299 --> 00:47:25,509
[Sunok] Don't let her ruin
her life any further.

864
00:47:25,843 --> 00:47:28,429
Keep her out of prison
and safe from bad men.

865
00:47:28,512 --> 00:47:29,805
[sniffles]

866
00:47:29,889 --> 00:47:31,390
You're a police officer.

867
00:47:31,974 --> 00:47:33,017
And her dad.

868
00:47:33,601 --> 00:47:36,687
- So you need to protect your daughter now.
- [Jinman] Enough.

869
00:47:38,272 --> 00:47:39,440
[exhales]
Hey.

870
00:47:40,858 --> 00:47:43,444
Listen, I just have to ask,
how am I supposed to believe you?

871
00:47:43,903 --> 00:47:44,904
Huh?

872
00:47:45,696 --> 00:47:48,949
You were a working girl.
A lady of the night.

873
00:47:49,033 --> 00:47:50,284
[Sunok] What?

874
00:47:50,368 --> 00:47:51,619
[scoffs]

875
00:47:51,702 --> 00:47:53,287
You mean when I was a hostess?

876
00:47:53,996 --> 00:47:54,997
[Jinman] Yeah.

877
00:47:55,289 --> 00:47:56,290
I mean...

878
00:47:57,041 --> 00:47:59,460
...seriously, how the fuck would
I know whose daughter she is?

879
00:48:00,044 --> 00:48:01,045
I wouldn't.

880
00:48:01,128 --> 00:48:02,213
I do, though.

881
00:48:03,881 --> 00:48:05,508
You were the only one I was with then.

882
00:48:10,721 --> 00:48:13,432
[inhales]
Shit, this is really fucked.

883
00:48:17,686 --> 00:48:19,271
[Jinman groans]

884
00:48:20,815 --> 00:48:22,233
[smacks lips]

885
00:48:22,316 --> 00:48:23,984
[Jinman] Shit.

886
00:48:27,571 --> 00:48:28,572
[clicks tongue]

887
00:48:29,907 --> 00:48:34,036
Hey. Have you told her, you know, that-

888
00:48:34,120 --> 00:48:35,704
that I'm, uh-I'm her dad?

889
00:48:35,788 --> 00:48:37,581
Or, does she know?

890
00:48:38,541 --> 00:48:39,583
I haven't.

891
00:48:41,168 --> 00:48:43,003
Heeju believes her father's dead.

892
00:48:45,798 --> 00:48:49,844
Would you tell your daughter
that her father was a gambling addict...

893
00:48:50,803 --> 00:48:52,763
...who ran off and abandoned her?

894
00:48:53,431 --> 00:48:54,974
That's good, then, yeah?

895
00:48:55,558 --> 00:48:57,309
Just keep it that way, okay?

896
00:48:58,102 --> 00:49:00,187
'Cause I-
I'm not her father.

897
00:49:00,271 --> 00:49:02,356
[Jinman] Got it?
Don't tell her.

898
00:49:03,065 --> 00:49:05,943
If you tell her I'm her father,
or anything like that,

899
00:49:06,026 --> 00:49:09,488
you, me, and her,
we're all gonna be fucked.

900
00:49:11,490 --> 00:49:13,242
The three of us will die.

901
00:49:13,325 --> 00:49:14,326
[Jinman] Understand?

902
00:49:15,494 --> 00:49:17,496
So stop saying nonsense.

903
00:49:18,414 --> 00:49:19,582
Seriously.

904
00:49:19,665 --> 00:49:20,666
[clicks tongue]

905
00:49:31,427 --> 00:49:34,221
[door opens and closes]

906
00:49:34,305 --> 00:49:35,806
[exhales]

907
00:49:48,944 --> 00:49:50,237
[brakes squeak]

908
00:49:51,947 --> 00:49:54,950
[chains rattling]

909
00:50:01,999 --> 00:50:05,002
[door scraping]

910
00:50:21,310 --> 00:50:22,603
[brakes squeak]

911
00:50:32,363 --> 00:50:33,989
[beeping]

912
00:50:37,201 --> 00:50:38,661
[creaking]

913
00:50:47,586 --> 00:50:49,296
[exhales]

914
00:50:50,256 --> 00:50:52,925
[Heeju] <i>Mokcheon Port, 9:00 p.m. tomorrow.</i>

915
00:50:55,386 --> 00:50:56,428
<i>See you there.</i>

916
00:51:05,145 --> 00:51:08,148
[inhales and exhales sharply]

917
00:51:10,901 --> 00:51:13,904
[cell phone vibrating]

918
00:51:16,115 --> 00:51:18,450
INCOMING CALL
AUNTIE MIJA

919
00:51:20,411 --> 00:51:21,870
Hey, Auntie.

920
00:51:22,371 --> 00:51:23,664
Hey.

921
00:51:23,747 --> 00:51:25,124
Are you coming today?

922
00:51:27,042 --> 00:51:28,586
[Mija] <i>Why aren't you saying anything?</i>

923
00:51:28,669 --> 00:51:29,753
<i>[exhales]</i>

924
00:51:29,837 --> 00:51:32,881
<i>You should be here.</i>
<i>Your mom might be dying.</i>

925
00:51:33,465 --> 00:51:35,634
<i>Ah, I just have a bad feeling.</i>

926
00:51:35,718 --> 00:51:37,386
<i>I really think you should come.</i>

927
00:51:39,471 --> 00:51:40,556
Okay.

928
00:51:45,436 --> 00:51:46,645
[exhales]

929
00:51:51,650 --> 00:51:52,776
[Mija] Sunok.

930
00:51:53,277 --> 00:51:54,945
Everything will be all right.

931
00:51:55,654 --> 00:51:57,990
Just stay calm. Okay?

932
00:51:58,782 --> 00:51:59,783
RESTRICTED AREA
AUTHORIZED PERSONNEL ONLY

933
00:51:59,867 --> 00:52:02,161
Oh, and Heeju will be here soon.

934
00:52:02,828 --> 00:52:03,871
See you later!

935
00:52:04,705 --> 00:52:07,708
[♪ dramatic music]

936
00:52:13,589 --> 00:52:19,261
GANGWON SAEBAEK HOSPITAL

937
00:52:20,304 --> 00:52:21,764
[Heeju] <i>Is it over already?</i>

938
00:52:21,847 --> 00:52:22,848
Yeah.

939
00:52:22,931 --> 00:52:24,058
[sniffs]

940
00:52:24,808 --> 00:52:26,602
They closed her up right away.

941
00:52:28,854 --> 00:52:31,273
I spoke with the doctor
before I called you.

942
00:52:32,066 --> 00:52:34,693
They said from here on out,
chemo won't help her.

943
00:52:36,695 --> 00:52:38,322
So she should go home.

944
00:52:38,781 --> 00:52:40,991
And spend the rest
of her time with family.

945
00:52:41,075 --> 00:52:43,160
[breathing shakily]

946
00:52:43,243 --> 00:52:44,536
Where are you right now?

947
00:52:45,621 --> 00:52:47,206
Why aren't you over here?

948
00:52:50,668 --> 00:52:51,752
[phone beeps]

949
00:52:55,964 --> 00:52:57,424
[shudders]

950
00:53:01,637 --> 00:53:04,640
<i>[machines beeping]</i>

951
00:53:07,059 --> 00:53:10,062
[♪ dramatic music]

952
00:53:18,320 --> 00:53:19,780
Hi, Mom.

953
00:53:30,457 --> 00:53:33,585
GANGWON SAEBAEK HOSPITAL
EMERGENCY CENTER

954
00:53:36,046 --> 00:53:39,049
[breathing heavily]

955
00:54:09,496 --> 00:54:12,499
[♪ dramatic music continues]

956
00:54:40,527 --> 00:54:43,530
[♪ music continues]
